Patch summary:
Support x86_64-to-ARM64 native bridge installs by forcing translated APK native
libraries to be extracted as real files when the selected ABI is bridged. Some
apps are marked as not requiring native library extraction, which is fine for
normal same-ISA execution but unreliable for translated ARM64-on-x86_64 execution.

This patch keeps the normal package manager ABI selection flow intact and adds
the special extraction path only after a bridged ABI has been selected. That
keeps native apps on the existing fast path while making translated apps usable.

